Quote:  [Leaves from a (wharf)  loafer's Journal] My dingy acquaintance [on the wharves] chuckles mockingly as he replies. `Not so bad for you, old un, though you're young at the profession yet. I

twigged you on your speeling lay. [fn `card sharping'] this afternoon whilst I was gattering my clay [fn `drinking beer']. No tricks on old soldiers. Give us a draw of the pipe.
